From: tag-click-hitbox-fix patch
Subject: [PATCH] Use TAGW for tag click hit-testing

The tagpad patch switched the tag-drawing loop in drawbar() to use TAGW,
but left buttonpress() using TEXTW. That meant the visible tag cells got
narrower while their clickable regions stayed at the old (wider) width,
so clicks had to land beyond the visible cell to register. This aligns
the hit-test with what's actually drawn.

---
 dwm.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/dwm.c b/dwm.c
--- a/dwm.c
+++ b/dwm.c
@@ -589,7 +589,7 @@ buttonpress(XEvent *e)
 	if (ev->window == selmon->barwin) {
 		i = x = 0;
 		do
-			x += TEXTW(tags[i]);
+			x += TAGW(tags[i]);
 		while (ev->x >= x && ++i < LENGTH(tags));
 		if (i < LENGTH(tags)) {
 			click = ClkTagBar;
